name: vmware
description: VMware managed object root assignements This module defines the VMware SNMP MIB root and its primary subtrees.

children.name: vmwNotifications
children.description: Parent of all notifications (traps, informs).

children.name: vmwEnvHardwareEvent
children.description: This notification, if the agent is so configured, may be sent when the system has detected a material change in physical condition of the hardware

children.name: vmwSystem
children.description: Parent of all managed objects relating to system software identification.

children.name: vmwVirtMachines
children.description: Parent of all managed objects relating to virtual machine inventory.

children.name: vmwVmTable
children.description: A table containing information on virtual machines that have been configured on the system.

children.name: vmwVmEntry
children.description: Identifies a registered VM on this ESX system.

children.name: vmwVmIdx
children.description: An operational identifier given the VM when registered on this ESX system. The value is not unique across ESX systems and may change upon reboot. VIM property: ha-vm-folder MOB: https://esx.example.com/mob/?moid=ha%2dfolder%2dvm A given Virtual Machine Instance can be queried using this URL: MOB: https://esx.example.com/mob/?moid=vmwVmIdx

children.name: vmwVmDisplayName
children.description: Name by which this vm is displayed. It is not guaranteed to be unique. MOB: https://esx.example.com/mob/?moid=vmwVmIdx&doPath=summary%2eguest

children.name: vmwVmConfigFile
children.description: Path to the configuration file for this vm expressed as a fully qualified path name in POSIX or DOS extended format VM Config file File name: MOB: https://esx.example.com/mob/?moid=vmwVmIdx&doPath=config%2efiles VM Datastore containing the filename: MOB: https://esx.example.com/mob/?moid=vmwVmIdx&doPath=config%2edatastoreUrl

children.name: vmwVmGuestOS
children.description: Operating system running on this vm. This value corresponds to the value specified when creating the VM and unless set correctly may differ from the actual OS running. Will return one of the values if set in order: Vim.Vm.GuestInfo.guestFullName Vim.Vm.GuestInfo.guestId Vim.Vm.GuestInfo.guestFamily MOB: https://esx.example.com/mob/?moid=vmwVmIdx&doPath=guest where moid = vmwVmIdx. If VMware Tools is not running, value will be of form 'E: error message'

children.name: vmwVmMemSize
children.description: Memory configured for this virtual machine. Memory > MAX Integer32 is reported as max integer32. VIM Property: memoryMB MOB: https://esx.example.com/mob/?moid=vmwVmIdx&doPath=config%2ehardware

children.name: vmwVmState
children.description: Power state of the virtual machine. VIM Property: powerState MOB: https://esx.example.com/mob/?moid=vmwVmIdx&doPath=summary%2eruntime

children.name: vmwVmVMID
children.description: No longer provided, use vmwVmIdx. See vmwVmUUID for cross system, unique, persistent identifier.

children.name: vmwVmGuestState
children.description: Operation mode of guest operating system. Values include: running - Guest is running normally. shuttingdown - Guest has a pending shutdown command. resetting - Guest has a pending reset command. standby - Guest has a pending standby command. notrunning - Guest is not running. unknown - Guest information is not available. VIM Property: guestState MOB: https://esx.example.com/mob/?moid=vmwVmIdx&doPath=guest

children.name: vmwVmCpus
children.description: Number of virtual CPUs assigned to this virtual machine. VIM Property: numCPU MOB: https://esx.example.com/mob/?moid=vmwVmIdx&doPath=config%2ehardware

children.name: vmwVmUUID
children.description: A unique identifier for this VM. Must be unique across a set of ESX systems managed by an instance of vSphere Center. Example value: 564d95d4-bff7-31fd-f20f-db2d808a8b32 VIM Property: uuid MOB: https://esx.example.com/mob/?moid=vmwVmIdx&doPath=config

children.name: vmwVmHbaTable
children.description: Table of host bus adapters (hba) for all vms in vmwVmTable.

children.name: vmwVmHbaEntry
children.description: Uniquely identifies a given virtual machine host bus adapter.

children.name: vmwHbaVmIdx
children.description: This number corresponds to the vmwVmIdx in vmwVmTable.

children.name: vmwVmHbaIdx
children.description: Uniquely identifies a given Host Bus adapter in this VM. May change across system reboots.

children.name: vmwHbaNum
children.description: The name of the hba as it appears in the VM Settings. VIM Property: Virtual Device index of 200-299. MOB: https://esx.example.com/mob/?moid=vmwVmIdx&doPath=config%2ehardware

children.name: vmwHbaVirtDev
children.description: The oem host bus adapter hardware being emulated to the Guest OS. MOB: Not visible.

children.name: vmwHbaTgtTable
children.description: Table of all virtual disks configured for vms in vmwVmTable.

children.name: vmwHbaTgtEntry
children.description: Identifies a specific storage disk. Index may change across reboots.

children.name: vmwHbaTgtVmIdx
children.description: This number corresponds to vmwVmIdx in vmwVmTable.

children.name: vmwHbaTgtIdx
children.description: This value identifies a particular disk.

children.name: vmwHbaTgtNum
children.description: Identifies the disk as seen from the host bus controller VIM Property: Virtual Device's with index of 2000-2999,3000-3999. MOB: https://esx.example.com/mob/?moid=vmwVmIdx&doPath=config%2ehardware

children.name: vmwVmNetTable
children.description: Table of network adapters (nic) for all vms in vmwVmTable.

children.name: vmwVmNetEntry
children.description: Identifies a particular nic for the specified vmwVmIdx

children.name: vmwVmNetVmIdx
children.description: This number corresponds to vmwVmIdx in vmwVmTable.

children.name: vmwVmNetIdx
children.description: Identifies a unique network adapter in this table. Not guaranteed to be the same across system reboots.

children.name: vmwVmNetNum
children.description: The name of the device as it appears in the VM Settings. VIM Property: Virtual Device's with index of 4000-4999. MOB: https://esx.example.com/mob/?moid=vmwVmIdx&doPath=config%2ehardware

children.name: vmwVmNetName
children.description: What this virutal nic is connected to such as a virtual switch portgroup identifier. VIM Property: Virtual Device's with index of 4000-4999. MOB: https://esx.example.com/mob/?moid=vmwVmIdx&doPath=config%2ehardware then select property 'backing' to how this nic connects. If no backing was defined by operator, string will start with W: If unavailable, string will start with E:

children.name: vmwVmNetConnType
children.description: Do not use this value, and should an agent return it discard it.

children.name: vmwVmNetConnected
children.description: Reports 'true' if the ethernet virtual device is connected to the virtual machine.

children.name: vmwVmMAC
children.description: Reports the configured virtual hardware MAC address. If VMware Tools is not running, or VM has not yet been powered on for the first time and mac is to be generated by VM then the value is zero'd out/empty. VIM Property: Virtual Device's with index of 4000-4999. MOB: https://esx.example.com/mob/?moid=vmwVmIdx&doPath=config%2ehardware

children.name: vmwFloppyTable
children.description: Table of floppy drives for all vms in vmwVmTable.

children.name: vmwFloppyEntry
children.description: Identifies one specific floppy device. May change across system reboots.

children.name: vmwFdVmIdx
children.description: This number corresponds to vmwVmIdx in vmwVmTable.

children.name: vmwFdIdx
children.description: Identifies one specific virtual floppy device.

children.name: vmwFdName
children.description: File or Device that this device is connected to, example /dev/fd0. VIM Property: Virtual Device's with index of 8000-8999. MOB: https://esx.example.com/mob/?moid=vmwVmIdx&doPath=config%2ehardware If no backing was defined by operator, string will start with W: If unavailable, string will start with E:

children.name: vmwFdConnected
children.description: Reports 'true' if the floppy drive virtual device is connected to the virtual machine.

children.name: vmwCdromTable
children.description: Table of DVD or CDROM drives for all vms in vmwVmTable.

children.name: vmwCdromEntry
children.description: Identifies a specific DVD or CDROM drive. Value may change across system reboots.

children.name: vmwCdVmIdx
children.description: This number corresponds to the vmwVmIdx the vmwVmTable.

children.name: vmwCdromIdx
children.description: Identifies the specific DVD or CDROM drive.

children.name: vmwCdromName
children.description: Reports the iso or device this virtual drive has been configured to use VIM Property: Virtual Device's with index of 3000-3999 (same as disks) MOB: https://esx.example.com/mob/?moid=vmwVmIdx&doPath=config%2ehardware then select property 'backing' to how this cdrom connects. If no backing was defined by operator, string will start with W: If unavailable, string will start with E:

children.name: vmwCdromConnected
children.description: Reports true if the dvd/cdrom is connected to the virtual machine.

children.name: vmwVmInfoMIB
children.description: This MIB module provides for monitoring of inventory and state via polling and notifications of state changes for virtual machines residing on this host system. This MIB module also provides a mapping beween SMI managed objects defined here and their corresponding VMware Virtual Infrastructure Management (VIM) API properties.

children.name: vmwResMIBBasicCompliance
children.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the VMWARE-RESOURCE-MIB.

children.name: vmwVmInfoGroup
children.description: These objects provide virtual machine details.

children.name: vmwVmInfoNotificationGroup
children.description: Group of objects describing notifications (traps).

children.name: vmwVmObsoleteGroup
children.description: Managed objects that should not be used.

children.name: vmwResources
children.description: Parent of all managed objects relating to resource utilization.

children.name: vmwProductSpecific
children.description: parent of objects specific to a given hardware/software product.

children.name: vmwESXNotifications
children.description: Parent of all ESX specific notifications (traps, informs).

children.name: vmwVmPoweredOn
children.description: This trap is sent when a virtual machine is powered on from a suspended or a powered off state. The origin of this event can be several: for instance may be operator initiated, existing vmx process reconnects to control subsystem. NOTE: vms powered up due to VMotion are not reported. Upon receiving this notification client applications should poll the vmwVmTable to obtain current status.

children.name: vmwVmPoweredOff
children.description: This trap is sent when a virtual machine is powered off. The origin of this event can be several: for instance may be operator initiated, vmx process terminating abnormally. NOTE: vms powered down due to VMotion are not reported. Upon receiving this notification client applications should poll the vmwVmTable to obtain current status.

children.name: vmwVmHBLost
children.description: This trap is sent when a virtual machine detects a loss in guest heartbeat. The Guest heartbeat is only sent if VMware Tools are installed in the Guest OS. Control process will send this event whenever it determines the number of guest heartbeats for a given period of time have not been received. Upon receiving this notification client applications should poll the vmwVmTable to obtain current status.

children.name: vmwVmHBDetected
children.description: This trap is sent when a virtual machine detects or regains the required number of guest heartbeats for a given period of time. This is only sent if VMware tools are installed in the Guest OS. Upon receiving this notification client applications should poll the vmwVmTable to obtain current status.

children.name: vmwVmSuspended
children.description: This trap is sent when a virtual machine is suspended. The origin of this event may be several: operator initiated, by software api clients, and by other means. Upon receiving this notification client applications should poll the vmwVmTable to obtain current status.

children.name: vmwESXEnvHardwareEvent
children.description: ESX Specific version of this notification, if the agent is so configured, may be sent when the ESX Operating System has detected a material change in physical condition of the hardware

children.name: vmwESXEnvHardwareAlert
children.description: A hardware alert as received from the Common Infrastructure Management (CIM) subsystem on this system.

children.name: vmwESXEnvBatteryAlert
children.description: A battery alert as received from the Common Infrastructure Management (CIM) subsystem on this system.

children.name: vmwESXEnvChassisAlert
children.description: A chassis alert as received from the Common Infrastructure Management (CIM) subsystem on this system.

children.name: vmwESXEnvThermalAlert
children.description: A cooling/thermal alert as received from the Common Infrastructure Management (CIM) subsystem on this system.

children.name: vmwESXEnvDiskAlert
children.description: A disk drive alert as received from the Common Infrastructure Management (CIM) subsystem on this system.

children.name: vmwESXEnvPowerAlert
children.description: A power suppply alert as received from the Common Infrastructure Management (CIM) subsystem on this system.

children.name: vmwESXEnvProcessorAlert
children.description: A IPMI processor alert as received from the Common Infrastructure Management (CIM) subsystem on this system.

children.name: vmwESXEnvMemoryAlert
children.description: A IPMI memory alert as received from the Common Infrastructure Management (CIM) subsystem on this system.

children.name: vmwESXEnvBIOSAlert
children.description: BIOS System Event Log alert as received from the Common Infrastructure Management (CIM) subsystem on this system.

children.name: vmkLoaded
children.description: Has the vmkernel been loaded? (yes/no)

children.name: vmwProducts
children.description: This MIB module provides the OID identifiers which are returned from SNMPv2-MIB sysObjectId for agents in specific VMware products.

children.name: vmwEnvNumber
children.description: Count of number of conceptual rows in vmwEnvTable

children.name: vmwEnvLastChange
children.description: The value of sysUptime when a conceptual row was added or deleted from this table

children.name: vmwEnvTable
children.description: This table is populated from monitoring subsystems such as IPMI One conceptual row is maintained for each reporting component. Conceptual rows are not persistent across device resets

children.name: vmwEnvEntry
children.description: One entry for each physical component reporting its status to ESX Operating System

children.name: vmwEnvIndex
children.description: A unique identifier that does not persist across management restarts

children.name: vmwSubsystemType
children.description: Hardware component reporting environmental state

children.name: vmwHardwareStatus
children.description: Last reported state of this component

children.name: vmwEventDescription
children.description: Human readable description of this event

children.name: vmwEnvHardwareTime
children.description: Value of sysUptime when vmwHardwareStatus was obtained

children.name: vmwEnvironmentalMIB
children.description: This MIB module identifies hardware components of a machine as provided by IPMI.

children.name: vmwEnvMIBBasicCompliance
children.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the VMWARE-ENV-MIB.

children.name: vmwEnvMIBBasicCompliance2
children.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the VMWARE-ENV-MIB.

children.name: vmwEnvMIBBasicCompliance3
children.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the VMWARE-ENV-MIB.

children.name: vmwEnvironmentGroup
children.description: These objects provide physical hardware environmental details.

children.name: vmwEnvNotificationGroup
children.description: Notifications related to physical subsystems.

children.name: vmwESXEnvNotificationGroup
children.description: ESX System specific notifications about physical subsystems.

children.name: vmwESXEnvNotificationGroup2
children.description: ESX System specific notifications about physical subsystems.

children.name: vmwEnvAlertGroup
children.description: These objects provide physical hardware environmental details as reported by CIM subsystem.

children.name: vmwEnvSource
children.description: The source being used to obtain hardware state. Enumeration: 'unknown': 1, 'sensors': 2, 'indications': 3.

children.name: vmwEnvInIndications
children.description: Number of HTTP POST msgs containing CIM Indications in XML as received by agent.

children.name: vmwEnvLastIn
children.description: sysUptime when agent last received an indication.

children.name: vmwEnvOutNotifications
children.description: Number of notifications (traps|informs) sent that originated as CIM indication.

children.name: vmwEnvInErrs
children.description: Number of CIM Indications that agent did not complete receipt of.

children.name: vmwEnvIndOidErrs
children.description: Number of CIM Indications having a MappingString qualifier for which the value was not a valid oid.

children.name: vmwEnvCvtValueErrs
children.description: Number of CIM Indication properties having a MappingString qualifier for which the cim value for the given cim type could not be converted.

children.name: vmwEnvCvtSyntaxErrs
children.description: Number of CIM Indication properties having a MappingString qualifier for which the cim type could not be converted to smi syntax.

children.name: vmwEnvCvtOidErrs
children.description: Number of CIM Indication properties having a MappingString qualifier for which the the oid was not valid.

children.name: vmwEnvGetClassErrs
children.description: Number of CIM GetClass operations over a given cim indication class and namespace could not be completed (timeout) or returned error.

children.name: vmwEnvPropertySkips
children.description: Number of CIM indications having properties which do not have MappingString qualifier in the class definition and were not converted, sent along with the notification.

children.name: vmwEnvIndicationSkips
children.description: Number of CIM indications recieved for which GetClass reported no MappingStrings qualifier and were not converted to a notification.

children.name: vmwEnvDescription
children.description: A short description of the Indication.

children.name: vmwEnvEventTime
children.description: The time and date the underlying event was first detected. May be set to the time the SNMP agent recieved the notification if in the incoming CIM indication the value is NULL due to the creating entity not being capable of providing this information. This value is based on the notion of local date and time of the Managed System Element generating the Indication.

children.name: vmwEnvIndicationTime
children.description: The time and date of creation of the underlying Indication received by the snmp agent. The property may be set to the time SNMP agent received the notification if the entity creating the Indication is not capable of determining this information and delivers a null IndicationTime property. Note that IndicationTime may be the same for two Indications that are generated in rapid succession.

children.name: vmwEnvPerceivedSeverity
children.description: An enumerated value that describes the severity of the Alert Indication from the notifier's point of view.

children.name: vmwEnvAlertType
children.description: Primary classification of the Indication.

children.name: vmwEnvSysCreationClassName
children.description: The scoping System's CreationClassName for the Provider generating this Indication.

children.name: vmwEnvAlertingElement
children.description: The identifying information of the entity (ie, the instance) for which this notification is generated. The property contains the CIM path of an CIM object instance, encoded as a string parameter - if the instance is modeled in the CIM Schema. If not a CIM instance, the property contains some identifying string that names the entity for which the Alert is generated. The path or identifying string is formatted per the AlertingElementFormat property.

children.name: vmwEnvAlertingFormat
children.description: The format of the AlertingManagedElement property is interpretable based upon the value of this property.

children.name: vmwEnvSystemName
children.description: The scoping System's Name for the Provider generating this message.

children.name: vmwEnvProviderName
children.description: The name of the CIM provider, a software module loaded into the CIM subsystem, generating this message.

children.name: vmwLdap
children.description: VMware specific LDAP schema definitions.

children.name: vmwTraps
children.description: Managed objects defined under this node are only visible in notifications varbind lists and can not be polled.

children.name: vmID / vmwVmID
children.description: This is the ID of the affected vm generating the trap. If the vmID is non-existent, (such as for a power-off trap) -1 is returned. / This holds the same value as vmwVmVMID of the affected vm generating the trap. to allow polling of the affected vm in vmwVmTable.

children.name: vmConfigFile / vmwVmConfigFilePath
children.description: This is the config file of the affected vm generating the trap. / This is the path to the config file of the affected vm generating the trap and is same as vmwVmTable vmwVmConfigFile. It is expressed as POSIX pathname.

children.name: vpxdVMName

children.name: vpxdOldStatus

children.name: vpxdNewStatus

children.name: vpxdObjValue
children.description: This is the current object value in the preceding traps.
